Bluetongue [BTV], Greece
------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 13 Nov 2017 from Mrs Chrysoula Dile, Head, Animal Health Directorate, Ministry of Rural Development and Food, Athens, Greece

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 22 Sep 2017
Date of confirmation of the event: 25 Sep 2017
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 29 Feb 2016
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Bluetongue virus
Serotype: 16
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (basic and advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (4)
Outbreak 1: Dodekanisa 1, Notio Aigaio [Dodecanese Islands, South Aegean]
Date of start of the outbreak: 22 Sep 2017
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Cattle / 70 / 1 / 0 / 0 / 0
Affected population: the outbreak refers to one sentinel bovine animal in the island of Kos, which, in the framework of serological surveillance, seroconverted on [22 Sep 2017] and, in which, subsequently, the serotype BTV 16 was detected, on [25 Sep 2017].

Outbreak 2: Dodekanisa 2, Notio Aigaio
Date of start of the outbreak: 27 Oct 2017
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Cattle / 48 / 1 / 0 / 0 / 0

Outbreak 3: Dodekanisa 1, Notio Aigaio
Date of start of the outbreak: 27 Oct 2017
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Cattle / 42 / 6 / 0 / 0 / 0
Sheep / 45 / 0 / 0 / 0 / 0

Outbreak 4: Dodekanisa 4, Notio Aigaio
Date of start of the outbreak: 2 Nov 2017
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Cattle / 10 / 1 / 0 / 0 / 0
Affected population: one bovine animal in the island of Kos which showed clinical signs of the disease (fever, salivation, nasal discharge), seroconverted on [2 Nov 2017] and in which, subsequently, the serotype BTV 16 was detected on [6 Nov 2017].

Summary of outbreaks:
Total outbreaks: 4
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 170 / 9 / 0 / 0 / 0
Sheep / 45 / 0 / 0 / 0 / 0
Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed in percentages]:
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 5.29 / 0 / 0 / 0
Sheep / 0 / 0 / - / 0
* Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country; surveillance outside containment and/or protection zone; surveillance within containment and/or protection zone; control of vectors; vector surveillance; vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists); no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Directorate of Athens Veterinary Center, Department of Molecular Diagnosis, FMD, Virological, Rickettsial and Exotic Diseases, Virology Laboratory (National laboratory)
